news.title: High-rise buildings get a major lifeline as Rajasthan government to provide tap water connections
news.para: “Highrise buildings in the state mostly depends on ground water resources to daily needs of the residents. This is not good for the ground water level in the state. We would be providing pipeline drinking water to all highrise buildings of the state,” Gehlot said.

news.title: Ludhiana: Civic body to commence issuance of NOCs against plots through suvidha kendras
news.para: The resolutions were approved during the meeting of MC general house held under the chairmanship of mayor Balkar Singh Sandhu and commissioner Dr Shena Aggarwal at MC Zone A office on Friday.

news.title: Property tax pending for 20 years in Ahmedabad? Pay dues, not interest
news.para: The revenue department of Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC) said property owners with tax pending for 20 years before the financial year 2020-21 will be eligible for this scheme.

news.title: Mysuru development body to develop 1,000 acre layout around Bommenahalli
news.para: Somashekar said the new layout will come up in Bommenahalli, Daripura and surrounding areas. Muda has decided to start surveying 250 acres of land in Bommenahalli in the initial stages of the development of the proposed layout.

news.title: Mormugao municipality to act against 32 unsafe buildings
news.para: Municipal authorities have identified 32 residential buildings that have been declared dangerous for human occupation.

news.title: Chennai civic body directs AEs to inspect building demolition safety measures
news.para: Assistant engineers have been asked to inspect the safety measures at building demolition sites within three days of the builder uploading the site photos on the corporation website.

news.title: Ranchi administration sets up panel to check building safety
news.para: “The committee has been tasked to investigate the safety compromised at the residential complex and submit a report at the earliest,” a statement issued by the district administration said.

news.title: All land records under one server, to help in seamless registrations in Delhi
news.para: The exercise, said officials, will not only help the sub-registrars to determine that the sale deed of the land or property, which has come to them for registry, is clean and have a proper chain of ownership but will also prevent the seller from running around to get no-objection certificate from the agency concerned.

news.title: Haryana RERA issues arrest warrant against Shree Vardhman Infrahome's directors
news.para: The court of the adjudicating officer, or AO, issued the warrant on February 7 after hearing the complaints of the allottee, HRERA said in a official statement.

news.title: Gurugram: Chintels Paradiso' residents hold candlelight march to mark one year of collapse
news.para: ​​Raising slogans like "Ghar Ke Badle Ghar" (a house for a house) and "Justice for Humanity, Justice for Chintels", the protesters marched to Deputy Commissioner (DC) Nishant Kumar Yadav's officer and submitted a memorandum to him listing their demands.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP directs structural audit companies to meet RWAs of 15 societies
news.para: The four audit agencies — Bureau Vertias, TPC Technical Projects Consultants, Vintech Consultants, and NNC Design International — were drafted in by the district administration in August last year.

news.title: Canara Bank cuts lending rates by 15 basis points
news.para: The revised Repo Linked Lending Rate (RLLR) of the bank with effect from February 12, Canara Bank said in a regulatory filing on Friday.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: 13 residential-cum-commercial prime plots offered by Cidco
news.para: The bidder registration has already begun and e-tendering process will be completed by February 13. Subsequently, the e-auction will be conducted on February 15.

news.title: NCLT allows MHADA plea over its Patra Chawl land
news.para: The NCLT said, it appeared that Guruashish “has violated the joint development agreement (JDA) …’’ and MHADA was well within its rights to terminate the arrangement with the builder.

news.title: JK Lakshmi Cement's net profit up 17.73% in Q3 FY23
news.para: JK Lakshmi Cement's consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,576.06 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 20.88 per cent from Rs 1,303.81 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.
